 moving, wanderers, quick respawns. All not condusive to a large raid. Also gives these ubers a chance to put it all on the line and test their &quot;real&quot; ability. You die in zone 4, you better have some backup equipment because you're gonna have to figh your way back to get your stuff.<br><br>Let's face it, the risk/reward for most places is nil. You never really have to fear that your gear may be lost forever. Here's a chance for the game to really bite back.<br><br>Will a 60 warrior chance his quest BP for a chance at getting a 90AC, 30str, 30sta, 30dex, 30agi, 500hp, effect:healing BP in zone 5?<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub96.ezboard.com/uaegonsoundforge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aegon Soundforge</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Level 13, Advanced Beggar</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/3/02 9:52:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub96.ezboard.com/fkanebaylecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=454.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Idea for the next expansion...</span><hr size=1> What you describe is basically what VP is like albeit for high levels and only one zone.  Unfortunately the risk vs reward for VP is such that it's not worth the hassle except as a diversion later on.<br><br>edit:  ok i missed the part about for 1-2 groups only. =p  It's an interesting idea.  Something like this would make an intersting addition to the game.  It's rare that you can actually do a dungeon crawl in a small exp group. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=281589">Aegon, 53 Bard</A> <br><A HREF= "http://www.shattered-sorcery.com/iv">In Virtue</A><br></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub96.ezboard.com/uaegonsoundforge.showPublicProfile?la